using a native serial config, which can include `java.util.ArrayList`. For array types, though, the config syntax might be a bit strange. So, it seems like I should use `ArrayList` with `java.util.ArrayList`. I think AssertJ equals can work for `ArrayList`, so I want to set up `List<String> expected = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList(...))` and check equality. I'm also wondering if context rejection affects AssertJ, and how it’s restored afterward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Editing access modifiers**\\n\\nI'm considering whether an inner class being public is okay. It seems to be permissible. Then I think about the test method; making it package-private feels appropriate as well. I definitely need to make some edits here to ensure everything aligns with the intended structure. It's small adjustments, but they can make a significant difference in the overall efficiency and accessibility of the code. Let's get to editing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NcjGfZGkNRiMQwCzY4K6vKPQ|fc_05573139d34d08010169f4e57c70b08195a0f72886a2d1f376", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.h2.api.JavaObjectSerializer;\nimport org.h2.engine.SysProperties;\nimport org.h2.util.JdbcUtils;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test {\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToObjectInputStreamWhenContextClassLoaderRejectsSerializedClass() {\n        assertThat(SysProperties.USE_THREAD_CONTEXT_CLASS_LOADER).isTrue();\n        List<String> payload = new ArrayList<String>(Arrays.asList(\"alpha\", \"beta\"));\n        JavaObjectSerializer configuredSerializer = JdbcUtils.serializer;\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n\n        JdbcUtils.serializer = null;\n        try {\n            byte[] serialized = JdbcUtils.serialize(payload, null);\n\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader());\n            Object decoded = JdbcUtils.deserialize(serialized, null);\n\n            assertThat(decoded).isEqualTo(payload);\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n            JdbcUtils.serializer = configuredSerializer;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class RejectingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        @Override\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage h2;\\n\\nimport org.h2.api.JavaObjectSerializer;\\nimport org.h2.engine.SysProperties;\\nimport org.h2.util.JdbcUtils;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.Arrays;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test {\\n    @Test\\n    void fallsBackToObjectInputStreamWhenContextClassLoaderRejectsSerializedClass() {\\n        assertThat(SysProperties.USE_THREAD_CONTEXT_CLASS_LOADER).isTrue();\\n        List<String> payload = new ArrayList<String>(Arrays.asList(\\\"alpha\\\", \\\"beta\\\"));\\n        JavaObjectSerializer configuredSerializer = JdbcUtils.serializer;\\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\\n\\n        JdbcUtils.serializer = null;\\n        try {\\n            byte[] serialized = JdbcUtils.serialize(payload, null);\\n\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader());\\n            Object decoded = JdbcUtils.deserialize(serialized, null);\\n\\n            assertThat(decoded).isEqualTo(payload);\\n        } finally {\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\\n            JdbcUtils.serializer = configuredSerializer;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class RejectingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\\n        @Override\\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 469, "output": 1234, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38567, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777657199536, "responseId": "resp_05573139d34d08010169f4e570176881959d2645846c556661"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_NcjGfZGkNRiMQwCzY4K6vKPQ|fc_05573139d34d08010169f4e57c70b08195a0f72886a2d1f376", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1698 bytes to tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777657214108}]}
